# Semgrep ignore — paths intentionally excluded with rationale.
#
# This file is read by `semgrep scan` (run from repo root). The pentest
# runner (backend/app/jobs/pentest_collectors.py:run_semgrep) invokes
# semgrep against /app/backend in the deployed container, so these
# exclusions also need a matching block when running inside the image.
# We use both .semgrepignore (root, dev workflow) and per-file paths
# below so coverage stays consistent across environments.

# --- Alembic migrations ---------------------------------------------------
# Migrations are DDL/DML by definition. The `text()` calls flagged by
# python.sqlalchemy.security.audit.avoid-sqlalchemy-text are author-written
# SQL run out-of-band by the operator, never reachable from web requests.
# This is a different trust boundary than the API layer; the rule does not
# apply.
backend/alembic/

# --- Pentest jobs (non-prod compliance tooling) ---------------------------
# Files under backend/app/jobs/pentest_*.py are the automated weekly
# self-assessment runner. They intentionally make dynamic outbound HTTP
# calls to:
#   - GCP / Identity Platform admin APIs (audience-locked OIDC)
#   - the deployed backend's own /api/admin/pentest/* endpoints
#   - operator-provided webhooks (Slack-style notifications)
# All URLs are constructed from runtime config, not user input. The
# python.lang.security.audit.dynamic-urllib-use-detected hits here are
# false positives. These scripts are also gated by Cloud Run job IAM and
# do not serve web traffic, so the API-surface trust model does not
# apply.
backend/app/jobs/pentest_collectors.py
backend/app/jobs/pentest_identity.py
backend/app/jobs/pentest_runner.py
backend/app/jobs/pentest_tenant.py

